#16965 merges the changes from that branch into here. Did it a PR into here since it is early and a sanity check would be nice
Looks good to me with the changes in https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/tree/mrb/5376. I'm really happy that this change ended up working out so well!
Looks good to me with the changes in https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/tree/mrb/5376. I'm really happy that this change ended up working out so well!

That we have to use `outParam`s in a subclass when `FunLike F M N` already has these `outParam`s is a bit weird, but it matches my experience (e.g. [here](https://leanprover.zulipchat.com/#narrow/stream/287929-mathlib4/topic/.60example.20.28p.20.3A.20P.29.20.3A.20Q.20.3A.3D.20p.60.20takes.200.2E25s.20to.20fail!/near/404670305)), and in particular it shouldn't cause any extra harm.

This change is extra good since it brings `AddMonoidHomClass` better in line with `MonoidHomClass` which already has `M N : outParam`.
Wouldn't this be fixed by making `M` an `outParam` in `ZeroMemClass S M`? Let me try...
I have a branch where I did this. Let me push it. (Alternately you can use `Ideal.zero_mem`)
I am still messing around with trying to remove the adaptation note for the Kummer extensions so changes around there might be spurious
There should probably be a library note about requiring `outParam`s

I can't figure out this one yet. Kummer extension notation (or maybe just `AdjoinRoot` itself) loses the coefficient ring in the search during `IsPrimitive.map_of_injective` resulting in a search for rings structures on a metavariable.
The notation itself is not great because `K` is not `K` from the context.
